5:
Hmm... I'm surprised elemental
shards and the study of them exist
in other worlds.
13:
Yo, what're you doing spacin' out
here?
17:
Ah, don't get me wrong. I appreciate
that you prepared a research space
for me. However...
22:
Do you still need something? We'd
be happy to help, whatever it is.
25:
I have adjusted accordingly to life in
another world, but there's still the
matter of procuring research
materialsâ€”elemental shards in
particular.
28:
Oh, if it's stuff you're looking for, want
to come along with us? We're just
about to head out, actually.
34:
Hahahaha! Nobody told me there'd
be ample opportunity for combat!
This is PERFECT! Time for some
practical application!
37:
More data! WONDERFUL! I knew I was
right to prepare beforehand!
Hahahaha!
42: The hell is wrong with this guy?
46:
Honestly... I'm kinda freaked out right
now.
50:
Bryce does get very excited when he
experiments.
54:
That was the last one. Thank you for
this. Not only was I able to procure
the shards, but I also collected a
good amount of data.
59:
Is that all you have to say?! You
nearly hit us!
63:
Haven't I told you before? I always
take care to aim properly. Besides,
even if I were to make a mistake, I
have treatment prepared.
68:
How the hell were we supposed to
know that? You gotta explain these
things before we're in the danger
zone!
70:
Just 'cause you're not worried,
doesn't mean the rest of us aren't!
75:
I see. It makes sense that you're
angry.
77:
If I alone am the only informed
party, then you have every right to
doubt my opinion and your safety.
80:
My apologies. How about I explain
on the way back? Better late than
never.
86:
Another failure on my part... Why is it
that I never learn?
88:
Even though I proudly boasted to
him before...
92: But I'm right. I know I am.
94:
The results speak for themselves.
These techniques won't be what
causes strife... Right?
102:
Oh, it's you. Forget that. I was
muttering to myself.
104:
Did you come for another lecture?
You're quite the peculiar one.
108: Yes, I wish to learn more.
111:
Suit yourself. I hope you have time
set aside, though. This will be
lengthy.
119:
...And that concludes my summary
on recycling elemental shards. As
you can see, it shows promise as a
sustainable source of energy.
122:
To restore their light and give them
purpose again...
124:
This is an impressive technology you
discovered.
128:
I can't claim all the credit. Besides, it
possesses a significant flaw.
131:
There is a slight chance that the
energy will surge beyond
controlâ€”which is a risk that can't be
ignored.
134:
All my time since being exiled from
the Tartas Society has been
devoted to proving this conjecture.
138: So the lightless shards can't be used?
141:
...No, they can. The probability that
there ISN'T a problem is higher.
143:
It's more likely that all my research is
for naught...
146:
Completely useless, just like inert
shards. Hehe, oh, the irony...
149:
Why do you continue this research
then?
152: What do you still have left to do?
156:
Alchemy is for the sake of others. For
the sake of the future...
158:
But I can't bring myself to move on. I
have to do this...
166:
Recycling a large amount of
elemental shards at once has a
chance of warping the mana.
169:
If it begins to release unstable
energy... It will be too late to stop an
accident once things are set in
motion. You know this, Frank.
172:
Hehehe... It's been quite a while
since we've argued like this.
174:
How miniscule of a chance are we
talking about anyway? You've
always been so paranoid about
everything, obsessed with
thoroughness.
175:
This technology will save our
drowning world. Have more
confidence in your life's defining
work!
178:
...That is all the more reason to
investigate. We can't risk lives at this
stage.
181:
It's too late, Bryce. Our sponsors are
already moving things along, and
I'm planning on doing whatever they
tell me.
183:
Alchemy has the power to change
the world, remember?
185:
And now I'm at the top of ours. All it
would take is a simple command,
and you'd be removed from our
society. But I'd rather we avoided
that.
188:
This is not what alchemy is meant
for...
197:
I'll see this research through. I have
to...
